            <ObservedData>
              <Attribute Type="Description">In a family with retinitis pigmentosa-3 (300029), Kirschner et al. (1999) identified deletion of exon 15A of the RPGR gene. The splice variant containing exon 15A is expressed only in the retina. The phenotype was of retinal dystrophy with relatively late onset of night blindness, around the age of 10 years. From 30 years of age, very rapid deterioration took place and led to blindness by the age of 37 years. Electrophysiologically, the retinopathy appeared as a cone-rod dystrophy.</Attribute>
